net.hudup.core.data

Interface Dataset

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataset, KBasePointer, Pointer, Scanner, ScannerImpl, SemiScanner, SemiScannerExt, ServerPointer, Snapshot, SnapshotImpl

    public interface Dataset
extends Cloneable
    Interface of recommendation database which is called conventionally dataset. Dataset is one of the most important interfaces. Dataset includes essentially rating matrix, user profiles, item profiles and context information. There are two typical Dataset such as Snapshot and Scanner. Snapshot or scanner is defined as an image of piece of Dataset and knowledge base (KBase) at certain time point. This image is stored in share memory for fast access because it takes long time to access data and knowledge stored in hard disk. The difference between Snapshot and Scanner that Snapshot copies whole piece of data into memory while scanner is merely a reference to such data piece. Snapshot consumes much more memory but gives faster access and is more convenient. Snapshot and Scanner are read-only objects because they provide only read operator.
    Another additional Dataset is Pointer. Pointer does not contain any information nor provide any access means to dataset. It only points to another Snapshot or Scanner.
    Although you can create your own Dataset, Dataset is often retrieved from utility class parsers that implement interface DatasetParser. Snapshot is retrieved from SnapshotParser. Scanner is retrieved from ScannerParser. Both SnapshotParser and ScannerParser implement interface DatasetParser. Pointer is retrieved from Indicator. Indicator is DatasetParser specified to create Pointer.

    Within Hudup framework, Data layer is responsible for manipulating recommendation data organized into two following formats:
    • Low-level format is structured as rating matrix whose each row consists of user ratings on items, often called raw data. Another low-level format is Dataset which consists of rating matrix and other information such as user profile, item profile and contextual information. Dataset can be considered as intermediate format when it is modeled as complex and independent entity. Dataset is the most popular format.
    • High-level format contains fine-grained information and knowledge extracted from raw data and Dataset, for example, user interests and user purchasing pattern; besides, it may have internal inference mechanism which allows us to deduce new knowledge. High-level format structure is called knowledge base or KBase in short. KBase is less popular than Dataset because it is only used by recommendation algorithms while Dataset is exploited widely.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • isExclusive

        boolean isExclusive()
        Checking whether or not this Dataset is exclusive. Dataset is often loaded and feed to the Recommender algorithm via method Recommender#setup(Dataset, Object...). If this Dataset is in exclusive mode, it is clear (method clear() is called) when method Recommender#unsetup() is called (Recommender algorithm is stopped).
        Returns:
        Whether or not this Dataset is exclusive

      • setExclusive

        void setExclusive(boolean exclusive)
        Setting whether or not this Dataset is exclusive. Dataset is often loaded and feed to the Recommender algorithm via method Recommender#setup(Dataset, Object...). If this Dataset is in exclusive mode, it is clear (method clear() is called) when method Recommender#unsetup() is called (Recommender algorithm is stopped).
        Parameters:
        exclusive - indicates whether or not this Dataset is exclusive

      • getCTSchema

        ContextTemplateSchema getCTSchema()
        Getting schema of context template ContextTemplate. ContextTemplate is template for a context represented by the class Context. Context includes time, location, companion, etc. associated with a user when she/he is buying, studying, etc. For example, Time is the template for time context 31/10/2015 6:45. In other words, context is an instance of context template with specific value. A set of context templates is structured as the model which is called context template schema represented by interface ContextTemplateSchema. Please see Context, ContextTemplate and ContextTemplateSchema for more details of context, context template and context template schema.
        Returns:
        ContextTemplateSchema

      • getProvider

        Provider getProvider()
        Some datasets like Scanner uses Provider to retrieve information from database because such datasets do not store information in memory. However other datasets such as Snapshot do not implement this method. This method return the internal provider of scanner.
        Returns:
        internal provider of scanner.

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clearing this Dataset, deallocating memory of Dataset.
